Gusiam said:<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <br>
<br>
I believe raids like poh and pof should be schedled. I have lead those raids and know how much work is involved in those. Hot on the other hand you just slap 1 to 4 groups together and your good to go. Your best bet is when you want to do HoT. Let other dragon aligned guilds know that you plan on doing it a certain time. <br>
<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
<br>
Hmm now what would be an easy way to let the other dragon aligned guilds know that you were headed to HoT?   Hmm maybe the Calendar?  I am not saying don't slap a couple groups together and go to HoT, but if someone has posted on the Calendar, isn't that as good as getting a tell about it?<br>
<br>
Just a thought...<br>
<br>
Sinndar Solitaire<br>
Phantasmist of The Shadow Order <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uzxing.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zxing</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>h0x0r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(10/19/01 9:22:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumfrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1609.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: HoT on Calendar???</span><hr size=1> To respond to Sola, I didn't mean to sound hostile in my post. Just considering what Gusiam said, that one well equiped group can do HoT.<br>
<br>
As to HoT being on the calendar. Back when I was trying to lead HoT raids for Vita Infinita, Simc brought that question up. I posted that I didn't see a need for it to be on the calendar, but I would respect a raid that was posted. It seemed for the most part, that everyone felt that way. That it didn't need to be on the calendar, but people wouldn't ignore it either.<br>
<br>
If not, then my fault for being mistaken on that.<br>
<br>
And yes, like the lovely Neesha said, I am not a member of Vita Infinita, so it's only my own opinion. But I did a lot for Vita when I was a member, and know a good bit about HoT, along with other zones...which is why I posted. <p>Kodylan Stompioras
<br>Warlord of Fallen Legacy
<br>Lanys T`Vyl</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ugusiamroa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>GusiamROA</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>l33t d00d!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(10/19/01 9:37:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumfrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1609.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: HoT on Calendar???</span><hr size=1> Posting on the calender is not as good as getting a tell.  I haven't looked at the calender since I stoped hosting planes raids.  So for someone to send tells to officers or raid leaders of the,  what is there 4 guilds on dragon faction capable of doing HoT, a tell in game is way more effiecent.<br>
<br>
Gus  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ukitiari.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kitiari</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>p0\/\/3r-p0sT3r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(10/19/01 9:44:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumfrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1609.topic&index=18>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: HoT on Calendar???</span><hr size=1> Simc had asked whether HoT should be on the calendar after she saw a posted raid by Gyn.  We still feel using the calendar as a communication tool for HoT raiding is better then visiting each guild's web site or trying to track down raid leaders.  Even if 2 raids are planned for that day it is better to work out the detail before when you don't have 40 people waiting for a raid to start.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ubraskdembones.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Brask Dembones</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>h0x0r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(10/19/01 10:22:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumfrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1609.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: HoT on Calendar???</span><hr size=1> Just wanted to apologize to RoA if you felt this was targetted towards you guys, those weren't my intentions <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   I'd also like to apologize for my ignorance in that I wasn't even aware this discussion had occurred previously.<br>
<br>
Things change though, rules change, usually for the betterment of the server as a whole.  Was PoH always scheduled on the calendar? or did it only become an issue once more guilds became planar ready?  As I said before, my guild is getting ready for their first attempt at HoT, possibly within the next month or two.  Who is next?  4 guilds now? 6 guilds 1 month from now? 15 guilds 3 months from now?  What happens when one guild decides to park 3 groups in HoT and do it every night for 2 weeks straight?<br>
<br>
We adjusted our &quot;Rules&quot; in regards to Trak, is it time to do that for HoT,  regardless of what 4 guilds agreed upon in the past?<br>
<br>
I'm kind of split on this decision because if it remains FFA it allows me to do the 2 group thing whenever I want, but at the same time it makes it really difficult for smaller guilds finally getting the levels to do this type of raid.<br>
<br>
MW? RoA? TSO? GCR? SC? anyone else I missed.....what's your opinion on where we should go from here?<br>
<br>
Let me also add that I haven't looked at the calendar since I stopped going to Hate as well.  I'd be willing to change this though if it allowed for less conflicts. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uerrtai.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Errtai</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I live here.... get out.</span><br> <font color=#000033>(10/19/01 10:33:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumfrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1609.topic&index=21>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: HoT on Calendar???</span><hr size=1> Back in the day when we made that post on lanys.com General forum about shoukd HoT be FFA or not, there were a few guilds that were hanging out there.  Mithril Web, The Shadow Order, Leo/Cicely open mon/wed night raids, ROA, and I think Dark Trinity started going there eventually too (and before they went away Dark Trinity was in HOT more often than any other guild for a while)<br>
<br>
It was easy then for me to check on TSO, MW, DT if it wasn't a monday or wednesday night to make sure that we didn't conflict.  I never asked, I always said, &quot;just FYI riders is gonna be in HoT all day tommorrow&quot; or something like that.  If thye told me they had something big planned, I would work something out (usually just reschedule) but most of the time they said that would be fine.<br>
<br>
But not I didn't see hardly any &quot;guild only&quot; raids on HoT except for ROA.  This is why problems are coming up now.  More and more often people are trying to organize open HoT raids on any old days (we used to plan around monday and wednesday) and the calendar would benefit these people a LOT.  For ROA HoT farm is something that is for 18-24 people for a few hours, most of these raids have 36+ people with anyone level 52+ welcome it seems.<br>
<br>
Personally I feel really squeamish about supporting HoT on the calendar, because I don't want HoT to come down to calendar camping like POF and POH are.  <br>
<br>
Also: who is this Vipar guy in Vita?  Is he an officer or something?  He is the guy that I dealt with about the afformentioned raid that we didn't leave or move into the exit for.  I tried hard at first to work something out with him but he was a supreme ass, all he wanted to do was scream at me.<br>
 <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uerrtai.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Errtai</A> at: 10/19/01 10:35:50 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ubraskdembones.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Brask Dembones</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>h0x0r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(10/19/01 10:50:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumfrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1609.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: HoT on Calendar???</span><hr size=1> Okies, thanks Simc, Errtai <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    Sounds like you guys are more than willing to work with everyone on this.<br>
<br>
Vipar was the raid leader for Vita from the other night.  I haven't spoken with him outside of finding out the raid was cancelled so I don't really know the details of what happened.  I can see where you guys are coming from and don't think you did anything wrong that night, especially considering your past experience with how HoT scheduling was handled.  At the same time I can understand why Vipar may have been upset after taking the time to put his raid together along with a different understanding of HoT scheduling.  Hopefully both sides can take a step back and be understanding in this situation as any lingering ill-feelings only cause more problems in the future.<br>
<br>
I'll speak with my GL and have him take a peek in the private forum, if you need to contact me directly regarding that other issue you can use Brask@oboo.org<br>
